Not an ingredient normally found in beer, the fresh roasted pecans are South Louisiana-grown and are added during the brewing process along with Munich and Caramel malts â barley grains that are also known for imparting nutty flavor. This actively carbonated American brown ale pours a deep amber with a slight haze and the pecans stand out prominently in the nose.
